89
00:06:38.520 --> 00:06:41.422
Brian. You're not a reserve
agent anymore.

90
00:06:41.489 --> 00:06:42.590
You're on regular duty.

91
00:06:42.657 --> 00:06:43.892
You find a way
to cover this area.

92
00:06:43.958 --> 00:06:46.494
I don't want a fuckin' bird
landing in it.

93
00:06:46.561 --> 00:06:49.364
You.
Walk with me.

94
00:06:51.566 --> 00:06:54.169
Now's not the time to talk about
all the fights I'm in.

95
00:06:54.235 --> 00:06:57.271
Right now. this is the only
fight that matters.

96
00:06:57.338 --> 00:07:00.475
You have any idea
who did this?

97
00:07:00.542 --> 00:07:04.613
I know exactly who did it.

98
00:07:04.679 --> 00:07:06.180
Now we gotta go prove it...

99
00:07:11.218 --> 00:07:14.889
[CHANTING AND DRUMMING]

100
00:07:16.857 --> 00:07:19.093
You ever hear
of the Beck brothers?

101
00:07:19.160 --> 00:07:20.160
The Beck brothers?

102
00:07:20.227 --> 00:07:21.595
Yeah. the Beck brothers.

103
00:07:21.662 --> 00:07:24.165
They own about 300 gas
stations with slot machines.

104
00:07:24.232 --> 00:07:27.235
One of the brothers controls
the sale of liquor licenses.

105
00:07:27.302 --> 00:07:28.403
That could be a real problem.

106
00:07:28.470 --> 00:07:29.703
They don't want
our casino to happen.

107
00:07:29.771 --> 00:07:31.105
The casino's mine.

108
00:07:31.172 --> 00:07:32.973
And your hotel won't need
their liquor license.

109
00:07:33.040 --> 00:07:34.576
Once we annex the land.

110
00:07:34.641 --> 00:07:36.744
the state has no control
over anything we do.

111
00:07:36.811 --> 00:07:38.780
We didn't agree
to annexing the land.

112
00:07:38.847 --> 00:07:40.982
You don't need to...
we own the land now.

113
00:07:41.049 --> 00:07:42.917
That wasn't the deal...-

114
00:07:42.984 --> 00:07:44.553
- It's exactly the deal. Dan.

115
00:07:44.619 --> 00:07:47.321
And for you. it's priceless.

116
00:07:47.388 --> 00:07:48.956
There's no county permits
to build.

117
00:07:49.023 --> 00:07:51.292
The gaming license comes from
the Tribal Gaming Commission.

118
00:07:51.360 --> 00:07:52.794
as does your liquor license.

119
00:07:52.860 --> 00:07:55.530
your permit to operate.
and your hotel license...

120
00:07:55.597 --> 00:07:57.065
When you sold me the land. Dan.

121
00:07:57.131 --> 00:07:59.400
I gave you freedom
from oversight.

122
00:07:59.468 --> 00:08:00.501
Sidestepping those regulations

123
00:08:00.567 --> 00:08:01.802
is going to anger
a lot of people.

124
00:08:01.869 --> 00:08:03.804
That puts him in danger.
Both of you.

125
00:08:03.872 --> 00:08:06.975
That's why I have Mo.

126
00:08:07.042 --> 00:08:08.610
Who do you have?

127
00:08:08.677 --> 00:08:10.545
Surely you've learned by now...

128
00:08:10.612 --> 00:08:12.713
we're the only ones
playing by the rules.

129
00:08:12.780 --> 00:08:14.648
What are you saying?
You saying I need security?

130
00:08:14.715 --> 00:08:16.283
You've needed it
for a while. Dan.

131
00:08:16.350 --> 00:08:18.151
You should've learned that. too.

132
00:08:18.218 --> 00:08:21.255
[CHANTING AND DRUMMING]

133
00:08:30.298 --> 00:08:32.534
150 years ago.

134
00:08:32.599 --> 00:08:35.936
our people called
this land home.

135
00:08:36.003 --> 00:08:38.239
We drank from its rivers.

136
00:08:38.305 --> 00:08:40.575
we hunted its valleys.

137
00:08:40.641 --> 00:08:43.410
we cared for our dead
in these forests.

138
00:08:43.477 --> 00:08:46.213
we prayed on these mountains.

139
00:08:46.280 --> 00:08:50.218
This was our home.
And it nourished us.

140
00:08:50.285 --> 00:08:52.987
You understand our contract
with the reservation

141
00:08:53.054 --> 00:08:56.625
is invalidated the moment
they annex this land.

142
00:08:56.690 --> 00:08:59.626
You familiar with the term
indian giver?

143
00:08:59.694 --> 00:09:01.195
Well this is the opposite.

144
00:09:01.262 --> 00:09:05.065
The word you're looking for
is justice.

145
00:09:05.132 --> 00:09:07.501
By the power vested in me.

146
00:09:07.569 --> 00:09:10.204
I hereby claim this land
as property

147
00:09:10.271 --> 00:09:12.540
of the Nation
of Confederated Tribes

148
00:09:12.607 --> 00:09:14.242
at Broken Rock.

149
00:09:14.308 --> 00:09:17.446
[APPLAUSE]

150
00:09:19.314 --> 00:09:22.050
If he doesn't keep his word
I lose everything.

151
00:09:22.117 --> 00:09:24.584
If you were him
would you keep your word?

152
00:09:24.651 --> 00:09:28.288
It's worth the risk
if he is telling the truth.

153
00:09:28.356 --> 00:09:31.192
Trusting him
is not a business strategy.

154
00:09:31.258 --> 00:09:32.926
Dan!

155
00:09:32.993 --> 00:09:34.795
Come do the honors.

156
00:09:34.862 --> 00:09:37.999
Great. now he's asking you
to dig your own fucking grave.

157
00:09:42.270 --> 00:09:44.973
This is the beginning of
something very special. Dan.

158
00:09:45.040 --> 00:09:47.742
You watch what
a difference we make.

159
00:10:12.199 --> 00:10:14.434
Any endeavor that raises
my people's profile

160
00:10:14.501 --> 00:10:15.936
is a good one.

161
00:10:16.003 --> 00:10:19.372
but I wonder...
how many casinos do we need?

162
00:10:19.439 --> 00:10:21.342
Is this the right path
for our future?

163
00:10:21.409 --> 00:10:24.178
Are you challenging
Chairman Rainwater's leadership?

164
00:10:24.245 --> 00:10:25.880
I'm challenging his outlook.

165
00:10:25.947 --> 00:10:28.049
and what's best
for our people as a whole.

166
00:10:28.116 --> 00:10:30.218
instead of a select few.

167
00:10:32.087 --> 00:10:34.289
<i>In an historic
ground-breaking ceremony.</i>

168
00:10:34.356 --> 00:10:36.224
<i>Tribal Chairman Thomas
Rainwater</i>

169
00:10:36.290 --> 00:10:37.892
<i>annexed the land purchased</i>

170
00:10:37.958 --> 00:10:39.560
<i>for the Confederated Tribes
of Broken Rock's</i>

171
00:10:39.627 --> 00:10:42.262
<i>ambitious hotel
& casino project</i>

172
00:10:42.329 --> 00:10:43.931
<i>into the reservation.</i>

173
00:10:43.998 --> 00:10:46.267
<i>There are now questions
about what. if any.</i>

174
00:10:46.333 --> 00:10:48.203
<i>authority the state will
have over regulating</i>

175
00:10:48.270 --> 00:10:50.271
<i>the casino or monitoring
the construction</i>

176
00:10:50.338 --> 00:10:53.375
<i>of what will be the largest
hotel in the state.</i>

177
00:10:58.012 --> 00:11:00.381
Who's the contractor
on this build?

178
00:11:00.448 --> 00:11:02.083
I'll find out.

179
00:11:02.150 --> 00:11:04.685
I thought we were pretty
fucking clear with Mr. Jenkins.

180
00:11:04.751 --> 00:11:08.222
Well evidently not.

181
00:11:08.289 --> 00:11:11.025
We need to find
a less subtle means

182
00:11:11.092 --> 00:11:14.596
of expressing our displeasure.

183
00:11:14.661 --> 00:11:18.432
Can we bait that trap?

184
00:11:21.202 --> 00:11:24.206
I think it's time we spring it.

185
00:11:35.650 --> 00:11:38.019
So you think this
was intentional?

186
00:11:38.084 --> 00:11:39.487
I don't see tire
tracks anywhere.

187
00:11:39.553 --> 00:11:42.323
The fence is way over there...
no one threw it over.

188
00:11:42.390 --> 00:11:43.891
And it didn't fall
out of the fucking sky...

189
00:11:43.958 --> 00:11:46.761
That's exactly what it did.

190
00:11:46.828 --> 00:11:48.896
So you think someone
flew a plane over here

191
00:11:48.963 --> 00:11:50.463
and dropped clover
on your cattle

192
00:11:50.530 --> 00:11:51.833
in the middle of the night.
John?

193
00:11:51.900 --> 00:11:53.602
Think about that.

194
00:11:53.668 --> 00:11:55.336
We have.

195
00:11:55.402 --> 00:11:57.237
A King Air designed
for skydiving

196
00:11:57.304 --> 00:11:58.405
so it has a side door
large enough

197
00:11:58.473 --> 00:12:00.375
and could hold the weight.

198
00:12:00.440 --> 00:12:01.408
Why would anyone
do that. though?

199
00:12:01.476 --> 00:12:02.576
Who would do that?

200
00:12:02.642 --> 00:12:05.646
Your golfing buddy.
That's who.

201
00:12:05.713 --> 00:12:08.449
All right. John.
Think that.

202
00:12:08.516 --> 00:12:09.818
Now why the fuck am I here?

203
00:12:09.883 --> 00:12:12.820
I have no jurisdiction.
Cattle is your department.

204
00:12:12.886 --> 00:12:14.222
What can I do for you.

205
00:12:14.289 --> 00:12:16.223
I have six full-time
agents and four reserves.

206
00:12:16.290 --> 00:12:18.492
I don't have the manpower
for this investigation.

207
00:12:18.559 --> 00:12:20.294
I need your deputies...

208
00:12:20.361 --> 00:12:21.663
John. I can't
spare any deputies.

209
00:12:21.728 --> 00:12:22.729
County has more firefighters
sleeping at night

210
00:12:22.796 --> 00:12:23.730
than I have on patrol...

211
00:12:23.798 --> 00:12:25.133
You keep making my point.

212
00:12:25.199 --> 00:12:26.501
You wanna help?

213
00:12:26.568 --> 00:12:28.535
Give me deputies
or deputize my men.

214
00:12:28.602 --> 00:12:29.870
And not in six weeks...
right now.

215
00:12:29.936 --> 00:12:31.071
Right in this field.

216
00:12:31.139 --> 00:12:33.941
Which men?

217
00:12:34.007 --> 00:12:36.810
Him for starters.

218
00:12:36.877 --> 00:12:39.045
John. He put that drifter
on a soup diet

219
00:12:39.112 --> 00:12:41.348
and you want me to license him
to carry a weapon?!

220
00:12:41.415 --> 00:12:43.383
You mean the one who held
a knife to his throat...

221
00:12:43.450 --> 00:12:45.753
that drifter?

222
00:12:45.819 --> 00:12:47.122
You gonna tell me
that beating was worse

223
00:12:47.188 --> 00:12:50.324
than some of your officers
have doled out? Hmm?

224
00:12:53.328 --> 00:12:55.862
How many times have I stood
on a podium with you. Donnie.

225
00:12:55.929 --> 00:12:58.732
Stood for you.

226
00:12:58.800 --> 00:13:01.169
Think you'd be sheriff
if it weren't for me?

227
00:13:03.703 --> 00:13:04.872
Maybe you haven't noticed.

228
00:13:04.939 --> 00:13:08.809
but there's a war
going on in this valley.

229
00:13:08.876 --> 00:13:10.978
Today's the day
you choose sides.

230
00:13:15.649 --> 00:13:18.086
I'll issue the permit.
but he's got to understand...-

231
00:13:18.151 --> 00:13:19.853
- He's trained to use it.
- That's just great. John.

232
00:13:19.920 --> 00:13:22.523
Now you train him not to use it.

233
00:13:22.591 --> 00:13:24.559
If it comes out of
your holster. son.

234
00:13:24.626 --> 00:13:27.194
you'd better be an ironclad
reason. understood?

235
00:13:27.261 --> 00:13:28.730
Yeah.

236
00:13:32.132 --> 00:13:33.968
If he calls dispatch
for support.

237
00:13:34.035 --> 00:13:37.271
I expect you to give it to him.

238
00:13:37.338 --> 00:13:39.574
Did you hear me Donnie?

239
00:13:39.641 --> 00:13:40.775
I heard you Joh.

240
00:13:40.842 --> 00:13:43.278
The whole goddamn
valley heard you.

241
00:13:47.482 --> 00:13:49.083
We all know who did this.

242
00:13:49.149 --> 00:13:51.085
You find the evidence.

243
00:13:51.151 --> 00:13:53.854
And when he does.

244
00:13:53.921 --> 00:13:55.256
you drag him by the hair
back to me.

245
00:14:05.618 --> 00:14:08.554
I think we should ask for
an amendment to the agreement.

246
00:14:08.620 --> 00:14:12.859
- Something that...
- That what?

247
00:14:12.924 --> 00:14:15.026
Should he pinky swear
he won't fuck me?

248
00:14:20.198 --> 00:14:22.867
There's the skydiving
place in Three Forks.

249
00:14:22.934 --> 00:14:25.302
We're headed there now.

250
00:14:25.370 --> 00:14:27.239
And then there's other two

251
00:14:27.306 --> 00:14:28.740
<i>Missoula and Whitefish.</i>

252
00:14:28.807 --> 00:14:29.875
That's too far.

253
00:14:33.711 --> 00:14:37.783
Um. you didn't want
to mention the trust?

254
00:14:37.849 --> 00:14:39.017
<i>Trust who?</i>

255
00:14:39.083 --> 00:14:41.719
The trust.
The ranch is in a trust.

256
00:14:41.787 --> 00:14:42.954
It is?

257
00:14:43.020 --> 00:14:44.255
Yeah. don't play dumb
with me Kayce.

258
00:14:44.322 --> 00:14:45.191
I'm looking at your signature
right here.

259
00:14:45.256 --> 00:14:46.357
I ain't signed shit.

260
00:14:46.424 --> 00:14:48.559
[EXHALES]

261
00:14:48.626 --> 00:14:50.562
All right. Call me when you
get to Three Forks.

262
00:14:54.399 --> 00:14:56.201
My fucking family. man...

263
00:14:59.437 --> 00:15:03.042
Fuck. What the fuck. Beth?

264
00:15:15.721 --> 00:15:17.155
<i>Hi Jamie. It's Sarah.</i>

265
00:15:17.222 --> 00:15:19.123
<i>I just wanted to confirm
some facts with you...</i>

266
00:15:19.191 --> 00:15:21.393
Who's Sarah?

267
00:15:21.460 --> 00:15:23.796
Jumpy. jumpy. jumpy.

268
00:15:23.863 --> 00:15:25.531
What's got you so nervous.
I wonder.

269
00:15:25.596 --> 00:15:28.800
Well. you scared
the fucking shit out of me.

270
00:15:28.866 --> 00:15:32.102
And I'll tell you
what makes me nervous.

271
00:15:32.169 --> 00:15:35.039
This. Why a trust?

272
00:15:35.106 --> 00:15:36.707
You're an attorney. Jamie.

273
00:15:36.774 --> 00:15:38.343
I shouldn't have
to explain it to you.

274
00:15:38.410 --> 00:15:40.078
Okay. Why am I not in it?

275
00:15:40.144 --> 00:15:42.480
Do I really have to tell
you that too. Jamie?

276
00:15:42.547 --> 00:15:44.682
Here's all the things
I don't believe:

277
00:15:44.750 --> 00:15:47.352
I don't believe you're capable
of swallowing your pride

278
00:15:47.419 --> 00:15:49.620
and contributing to this family.

279
00:15:49.687 --> 00:15:52.124
I don't believe our father
will ever trust you again...

280
00:15:52.191 --> 00:15:54.225
which is why I don't believe you
have a role here anymore.

281
00:15:54.293 --> 00:15:57.596
Oh. You want to know
what my role is?

282
00:15:57.663 --> 00:15:59.697
Well I think you're
putting it in a trust

283
00:15:59.764 --> 00:16:03.235
so you can control the money.
So you can do this.

284
00:16:03.302 --> 00:16:05.537
And this. And this.

285
00:16:05.604 --> 00:16:07.973
The ranch is an investor. yes.

286
00:16:08.038 --> 00:16:10.241
How big an investor?

287
00:16:10.308 --> 00:16:11.842
I manage the finances. Beth.

288
00:16:11.909 --> 00:16:14.480
I need to know...
How big?

289
00:16:14.547 --> 00:16:17.282
Five million.

290
00:16:17.349 --> 00:16:19.217
I know. Jamie.

291
00:16:19.283 --> 00:16:22.321
You're worried about the risk.

292
00:16:22.388 --> 00:16:24.156
Two things: one...

293
00:16:24.221 --> 00:16:25.656
the risk is mitigated;

294
00:16:25.724 --> 00:16:27.993
two... if you didn't have balls
the size of quail eggs.

295
00:16:28.059 --> 00:16:30.094
you would've invested
this money years ago

296
00:16:30.162 --> 00:16:32.598
and he wouldn't be chasing
his fucking tail every fall.

297
00:16:32.663 --> 00:16:35.433
Good work.

298
00:16:35.500 --> 00:16:36.701
Hey. Beth.

299
00:16:36.769 --> 00:16:38.671
That is over half
the ranch's cash.

300
00:16:38.736 --> 00:16:42.373
What do we do in November
if cattle prices go down?

301
00:16:42.441 --> 00:16:45.043
How much money do you think
this ranch makes a year?

302
00:16:45.110 --> 00:16:47.012
After payroll and
property taxes

303
00:16:47.078 --> 00:16:48.479
and hay and countless
other expenses?!

304
00:16:48.547 --> 00:16:50.449
Nothing.

305
00:16:50.515 --> 00:16:53.051
This ranch has not turned
a profit in six years.

306
00:16:53.119 --> 00:16:54.786
And maybe you don't
understand the impact

307
00:16:54.852 --> 00:16:56.320
of a few hundred dead cattle.

308
00:16:56.388 --> 00:16:59.156
but that's half a million
dollars rotting in the field.

309
00:16:59.223 --> 00:17:00.458
You fucked us.

310
00:17:00.525 --> 00:17:03.061
Fucked us.

311
00:17:03.127 --> 00:17:05.563
I want the ranch out
and I want it out by today.

312
00:17:05.630 --> 00:17:07.065
It doesn't work
like that. Jamie

313
00:17:07.132 --> 00:17:09.500
You make it work like that.

314
00:17:09.567 --> 00:17:11.369
Fuck. now I see.

315
00:17:15.106 --> 00:17:16.741
You Think you're gonna
get him to trust you

316
00:17:16.808 --> 00:17:19.677
by making him not trust me?

317
00:17:19.744 --> 00:17:23.314
I wish you and your bird balls
the best of luck.

318
00:17:29.054 --> 00:17:33.859
["JOHNNY CASH"
BY BADD WOLF PLAYING]

319
00:17:39.131 --> 00:17:41.867
Afternoon!

320
00:17:41.933 --> 00:17:43.468
Can I help you?

321
00:17:43.535 --> 00:17:45.104
Could you get
a message to Jimmy?

322
00:17:45.170 --> 00:17:46.904
What's the message?

323
00:17:46.971 --> 00:17:49.473
This.

324
00:17:49.540 --> 00:17:51.109
Piece of shit.

325
00:17:51.175 --> 00:17:53.078
[GRUNTING]

326
00:18:02.287 --> 00:18:04.655
Tell him I want
my fucking money.

327
00:18:04.722 --> 00:18:06.826
He's got a week.

328
00:18:22.874 --> 00:18:25.309
How many total?

329
00:18:25.376 --> 00:18:30.081
So far we've found 360 more.

330
00:18:30.147 --> 00:18:32.451
Yeah they dropped bales
all the way up the valley.

331
00:18:32.518 --> 00:18:33.684
If we push the heard down here.

332
00:18:33.751 --> 00:18:35.119
they're gonna get
into that clover.

333
00:18:35.186 --> 00:18:37.888
I say we move them up the pass.
Through the mountains.

334
00:18:37.955 --> 00:18:39.858
That's an awful rough trail.

335
00:18:41.826 --> 00:18:44.229
Rip's right.

336
00:18:44.296 --> 00:18:46.998
We'll take them over the pass.

337
00:18:47.065 --> 00:18:49.067
That goddamn clover's
gonna take root.

338
00:18:49.134 --> 00:18:52.069
Next spring it'll be worse.

339
00:18:52.136 --> 00:18:55.173
We're gonna have
to burn this field.

340
00:18:55.240 --> 00:18:57.375
Just gotta be careful we don't
start a fucking forest fire.

341
00:18:57.442 --> 00:18:59.310
We'll bring up water trucks.

342
00:18:59.377 --> 00:19:01.813
I'll have the fire department
out here. just in case.

343
00:19:03.981 --> 00:19:06.750
I don't see any other way.

344
00:19:06.817 --> 00:19:07.853
Burn it.

345
00:19:07.919 --> 00:19:10.156
Yes sir.

346
00:19:20.482 --> 00:19:22.351
Colby.

347
00:19:22.417 --> 00:19:25.187
No horses.

348
00:19:26.889 --> 00:19:28.824
I hate this fucking thing.

349
00:19:35.030 --> 00:19:36.665
Rip.

350
00:19:38.399 --> 00:19:41.570
Who's the hell is that?

351
00:19:44.839 --> 00:19:48.444
Oh. what the fuck.

352
00:19:48.510 --> 00:19:50.480
How much do you owe?

353
00:19:55.585 --> 00:19:58.487
How much. Jimmy?

354
00:19:58.553 --> 00:20:00.822
Around eight thousand.

355
00:20:00.889 --> 00:20:03.291
I ain't got it.

356
00:20:03.358 --> 00:20:05.828
I know you don't.

357
00:20:05.895 --> 00:20:09.098
I'll get it.

358
00:20:09.165 --> 00:20:12.134
They said a week.

359
00:20:12.201 --> 00:20:15.838
Or I get this again.

360
00:20:15.905 --> 00:20:19.276
I'll get it.

361
00:20:26.482 --> 00:20:29.618
Cause of what we did.
they beat him?

362
00:20:31.820 --> 00:20:33.857
No. they beat him
for what I did.

363
00:20:37.993 --> 00:20:40.496
Has anyone heard
the term " ocean water"?

364
00:20:42.598 --> 00:20:45.067
It's a mixture
of Lysol and water.

365
00:20:45.134 --> 00:20:47.569
- Yeah. Genevieve.
- What do you do with it?

366
00:20:47.636 --> 00:20:49.238
You drink it.

367
00:20:49.305 --> 00:20:50.640
Why?

368
00:20:50.706 --> 00:20:53.309
Because alcohol is illegal
on the reservation.

369
00:20:53.376 --> 00:20:55.310
Because it's cheap.

370
00:20:55.377 --> 00:20:57.111
Because when people's
lives are miserable.

371
00:20:57.178 --> 00:21:00.715
they seek ways
to escape the pain.

372
00:21:00.782 --> 00:21:02.083
Ocean water is one way.

373
00:21:02.151 --> 00:21:04.687
It's a temporary escape.

374
00:21:04.753 --> 00:21:06.588
With painful repercussions.

375
00:21:06.655 --> 00:21:09.024
But when the misery's
bad enough.

376
00:21:09.091 --> 00:21:11.527
tomorrow is rarely
factored into decisions.

377
00:21:15.298 --> 00:21:19.135
Uh. so think of yourselves
as Sherlock Holmes.

378
00:21:19.202 --> 00:21:22.637
And your job is
to investigate the past.

379
00:21:22.704 --> 00:21:25.140
to understand the present.

380
00:21:34.050 --> 00:21:36.286
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

381
00:21:48.964 --> 00:21:52.100
Can I help you?

382
00:21:52.167 --> 00:21:53.770
Looking for John Dutton...-

383
00:21:53.836 --> 00:21:56.038
Yeah who's looking
for John Dutton?

384
00:21:56.105 --> 00:21:57.573
We don't know you.

385
00:21:57.639 --> 00:22:01.076
What the fuck
is this guy up to...

386
00:22:01.144 --> 00:22:02.945
Hey. step back.

387
00:22:09.851 --> 00:22:12.187
Hey!

388
00:22:12.253 --> 00:22:13.822
Come on motherfucker.
shoot me.

389
00:22:18.761 --> 00:22:19.862
Drop your weapon!

390
00:22:19.928 --> 00:22:21.563
You're fucking right.
Put it down.

391
00:22:32.942 --> 00:22:35.145
Oh fuck. Shit.

392
00:22:36.412 --> 00:22:38.815
Mister Dutton.

393
00:22:38.882 --> 00:22:41.751
seems all the stories
I've heard are true.

394
00:22:41.817 --> 00:22:42.919
Put it down. whoah.

395
00:22:42.985 --> 00:22:45.287
Whoah. everybody calm down.

396
00:22:45.355 --> 00:22:47.690
- Dad. This is...
- Malcolm Beck.

397
00:22:47.757 --> 00:22:51.360
This here is my brother. Teal.

398
00:22:51.426 --> 00:22:53.028
I apologize for everything
that's happened here.

399
00:22:53.095 --> 00:22:56.098
Misunderstandings aside.
we need to speak.

400
00:22:56.165 --> 00:22:58.966
Seems there's a problem
that we share.

401
00:22:59.033 --> 00:23:00.936
My problems
are squarely my own.

402
00:23:01.003 --> 00:23:03.606
Not this one.

403
00:23:03.673 --> 00:23:05.074
May we sit?

404
00:23:07.510 --> 00:23:09.444
We can talk under that tree.

405
00:23:09.511 --> 00:23:12.648
Uh-huh.

406
00:23:19.187 --> 00:23:20.823
What in the Sam-Hell
was that about?

407
00:23:20.889 --> 00:23:23.225
I'm sorry.
They called fifteen minutes ago

408
00:23:23.292 --> 00:23:25.060
I didn't know
they meant now.

409
00:23:25.127 --> 00:23:27.496
I'm taking this meeting alone.

410
00:23:29.498 --> 00:23:30.633
I said alone. Jamie.

411
00:23:39.943 --> 00:23:41.511
Don't you want to have
your lawyer present?

412
00:23:41.577 --> 00:23:45.948
This don't feel like
a lawyer meeting.

413
00:23:46.014 --> 00:23:49.350
I saw your son go against
Peabody Coal before the Senate.

414
00:23:49.417 --> 00:23:51.186
He's one hell of a litigator.

415
00:23:51.253 --> 00:23:52.887
Yeah. he can argue
with the best of them.

416
00:23:52.954 --> 00:23:56.524
So. what's this problem?

417
00:23:56.591 --> 00:23:58.360
A casino in this valley

418
00:23:58.426 --> 00:24:00.128
will have a negative affect
on our business.

419
00:24:00.194 --> 00:24:02.498
And for your ranch
and the others.

420
00:24:02.565 --> 00:24:04.967
In five years.
how many ranches like this

421
00:24:05.033 --> 00:24:06.968
can afford to exist?

422
00:24:07.036 --> 00:24:08.837
Wanna hear our guess.

423
00:24:08.904 --> 00:24:10.705
Soon as that casino opens.

424
00:24:10.772 --> 00:24:13.108
they'll approach the Forest
Service about a land lease.

425
00:24:13.175 --> 00:24:15.744
And they'll build a ski resort.

426
00:24:15.811 --> 00:24:17.045
And you know
as well as anyone.

427
00:24:17.113 --> 00:24:19.849
ski resorts are daggers
to the heart

428
00:24:19.915 --> 00:24:21.282
for places like this.

429
00:24:21.349 --> 00:24:23.452
It'll be an ocean of second
homes in ten years.

430
00:24:23.519 --> 00:24:24.720
I'm aware.

431
00:24:24.787 --> 00:24:26.655
I'm sure you are.

432
00:24:26.723 --> 00:24:28.723
Look. my office has no authority

433
00:24:28.790 --> 00:24:30.358
over an Indian casino.

434
00:24:30.425 --> 00:24:32.160
And yours has no authority
over the land.

435
00:24:32.228 --> 00:24:35.631
And your new AG
can't restrict them.

436
00:24:35.697 --> 00:24:38.567
That's why we need to fight
this outside the lines.

437
00:24:38.634 --> 00:24:40.703
We just don't think they have
the stomach for that.

438
00:24:40.770 --> 00:24:43.973
Yeah. well they have
the stomach for it.

439
00:24:46.575 --> 00:24:49.111
I don't need partners. fellas.

440
00:24:49.177 --> 00:24:51.647
Dan Jenkins has a partner.

441
00:24:51.713 --> 00:24:52.815
A big one.

442
00:24:52.882 --> 00:24:56.152
Think of us as allies.

443
00:24:56.219 --> 00:24:59.388
We'd be the perfect allies
for each other. John.

444
00:24:59.454 --> 00:25:01.557
Because there is no part of your
business that benefits ours.

445
00:25:01.624 --> 00:25:03.059
And vice versa.

446
00:25:03.126 --> 00:25:05.962
And when we fight.
it's a zero-sum game.

447
00:25:06.028 --> 00:25:09.665
We will win.
At any cost.

448
00:25:09.732 --> 00:25:12.402
Yeah.

449
00:25:12.467 --> 00:25:14.402
John...

450
00:25:14.470 --> 00:25:15.771
We just want you to consider it.

451
00:25:15.838 --> 00:25:18.707
I consider every option.
Malcolm.

452
00:25:18.773 --> 00:25:21.075
And I choose the one
that's best for my family.

453
00:25:21.143 --> 00:25:25.280
If it helps you.
it's a coincidence.

454
00:25:31.953 --> 00:25:34.089
That's not the way
you wear one of those.

455
00:25:55.543 --> 00:25:58.313
Working with them is a deal
with the devil. Dad.

456
00:25:59.548 --> 00:26:02.751
All the angels are gone. son.

457
00:26:02.818 --> 00:26:06.254
There's only devils left.

458
00:26:06.321 --> 00:26:08.123
At least they admit it.

459
00:26:15.297 --> 00:26:17.232
I'm impressed.

460
00:26:17.300 --> 00:26:19.233
You're really preaching.
That's good.

461
00:26:19.300 --> 00:26:21.169
Brushing up on your history?

462
00:26:21.236 --> 00:26:23.438
Just curious.
Wanted to see you teach.

463
00:26:23.505 --> 00:26:25.273
Glad I did.

464
00:26:25.340 --> 00:26:26.875
Be careful. though.

465
00:26:26.942 --> 00:26:29.645
If you only teach the tragedy.
they'll just see us as tragic.

466
00:26:29.712 --> 00:26:31.512
You should show them
the culture.

467
00:26:31.579 --> 00:26:33.682
Show them what
we're fighting for.

468
00:26:33.749 --> 00:26:35.217
And how do I do that.

469
00:26:35.283 --> 00:26:36.284
I dunno. Field trip. maybe?

470
00:26:36.351 --> 00:26:37.552
Bring 'em out to the rez.

471
00:26:37.618 --> 00:26:40.321
Everyone's getting ready
for the relay races.

472
00:26:40.388 --> 00:26:42.157
Can you think of a better way
to show them who we are?

473
00:26:42.223 --> 00:26:44.460
That's a really great idea.
I'll um...

474
00:26:44.527 --> 00:26:46.328
I'll talk to my administrator.

475
00:26:48.030 --> 00:26:49.264
Your rehab's in fifteen.

476
00:26:49.331 --> 00:26:51.232
Feel up to walking
to the rec center?

477
00:26:51.300 --> 00:26:53.969
Um. I-I can't.

478
00:26:54.036 --> 00:26:55.872
I've got a faculty meeting.

479
00:26:55.937 --> 00:27:00.175
I'll just call you
and reschedule. okay?

480
00:27:00.242 --> 00:27:03.111
Okay. Monica.

481
00:27:13.254 --> 00:27:15.424
No telling where that
son of a bitch got a plane.

482
00:27:15.491 --> 00:27:17.093
Not from skydivers.

483
00:27:17.158 --> 00:27:18.392
We're never going
to find it this way.

484
00:27:18.460 --> 00:27:20.562
He's smarter than that.

485
00:27:20.628 --> 00:27:22.098
[PHONE BUZZES]

486
00:27:25.835 --> 00:27:27.069
Pull over. would you?

487
00:27:37.946 --> 00:27:40.181
Hey.

488
00:27:40.249 --> 00:27:42.550
How are you?

489
00:27:42.617 --> 00:27:44.220
I'm lonely. Kayce.

490
00:27:44.287 --> 00:27:46.389
I can solve that problem.

491
00:27:46.454 --> 00:27:48.991
[LAUGHS]

492
00:27:49.057 --> 00:27:51.593
<i>I miss you.</i>

493
00:27:51.659 --> 00:27:53.561
Yeah. I miss you too.

494
00:27:53.628 --> 00:27:57.733
You... want me to come over?

495
00:27:58.966 --> 00:28:02.103
Yeah.

496
00:28:02.171 --> 00:28:03.806
But you can't. I just...

497
00:28:03.873 --> 00:28:07.009
Just wanted to hear your voice.

498
00:28:07.075 --> 00:28:09.311
I love you. Monica.

499
00:28:09.377 --> 00:28:11.446
God. I wish
that was all it took.

500
00:28:24.592 --> 00:28:26.327
Everything alright?

501
00:28:26.395 --> 00:28:28.897
Nope.

502
00:28:46.924 --> 00:28:49.060
The first thing we want
you to look into.

503
00:28:49.126 --> 00:28:52.730
is this Paradise Valley
Development Corporation.

504
00:28:52.797 --> 00:28:55.066
They've sold property
to the Broken Rock Tribe.

505
00:28:55.133 --> 00:28:58.202
which is attempting to annex it
into the reservation.

506
00:28:58.269 --> 00:29:00.404
We'd like you to file
an injunction against it...

507
00:29:00.471 --> 00:29:02.240
Can we contest that?

508
00:29:02.307 --> 00:29:04.976
I mean they're clearly attempt
to avoid state tax obligations

509
00:29:05.042 --> 00:29:07.644
and regulatory requirements.
I'd say we have a good chance.

510
00:29:07.711 --> 00:29:10.248
What about this Senate hearing
regarding jurisdiction

511
00:29:10.315 --> 00:29:12.750
violation by the Livestock
Association?

512
00:29:12.817 --> 00:29:15.052
Let me ask you a question.
Attorney General-elect.

513
00:29:15.119 --> 00:29:17.154
Do you find Jamie's
knowledge of the raid

514
00:29:17.221 --> 00:29:20.023
prior to it happening
inculpatory in any way?

515
00:29:20.090 --> 00:29:23.694
I'm concerned what happens
if they ask him to testify.

516
00:29:26.765 --> 00:29:28.066
Umm.

517
00:29:28.132 --> 00:29:31.169
I think attorney-client
privileges recuse of him.

518
00:29:31.236 --> 00:29:33.171
Even if he's aware of a crime
before it's happened.

519
00:29:33.238 --> 00:29:35.841
Are you saying a crime was
committed intentionally?

520
00:29:35.906 --> 00:29:39.410
There was no crime.

521
00:29:40.478 --> 00:29:43.881
Not the time.
Not the place.

522
00:29:43.948 --> 00:29:45.450
The concern is...

523
00:29:45.517 --> 00:29:46.785
the negative press
surrounding the hearing

524
00:29:46.852 --> 00:29:48.653
